## Variables

A value is datum (literal) such as a number or text.

There are different types of values:

* 323.3 is known as a float or double;
* 22 is an integer
* "Hello World!" is a string.

::: {.cell execution_count=1}
``` {.python .cell-code}
a = 10
print(a)
```

::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout}
```
10
```
